# Safarovo, Chishminsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Safarovo (; , Safar) is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Safarovsky Selsoviet, Chishminsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 991 as of 2010. There are 19 streets.
Geography
Safarovo is located 14 &nbsp; km southwest of Chishmy, the district's administrative centre. Karamaly is the nearest rural locality.
